<article>
    <h1>Splat Paint House</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201122/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-22"><time>2020-11-22</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>WHERE 207A Up­per Thom­son Road</p>
    <p>AD­MIS­SION Prices start at $36 a per­son for a starter pack­age that in­cludes a can­vas, paints and over­alls INFO www.splat­paint­house.com</p>
    <p>THE LOW­DOWN</p>
    <p>Art jam­ming stu­dio Splat Paint House opened as a pop-up venue in Joo Chiat. The re­sponse was so good that it has moved to a per­ma­nent space in Up­per Thom­son. It is said to be the only splat­ter paint stu­dio in Sin­ga­pore.</p>
    <p>FUN FAC­TOR</p>
    <p>I love paint­ing at home with my daugh­ters, but I hate clean­ing up the mess af­ter­wards. So imag­ine my glee at this stu­dio where the whole fam­ily can go crazy splash­ing paints with­out wor­ry­ing about spills or fin­ger­prints.</p>
    <p>While my el­der daugh­ter ex­per­i­ments with mix­ing colours for a self-por­trait, I un­leash my in­ner Jack­son Pol­lock and splat­ter out – what to my mind is – a mas­ter­piece.</p>
    <p>The vibe is friendly, non-judg­men­tal and wel­com­ing of painters of all skill lev­els.</p>
    <p>LEARN­ING VALUE</p>
    <p>There is more than one way to paint. Why stick to a brush when you can use all the tools – from tooth­brushes and sy­ringes to straws and “blow darts” – avail­able?</p>
    <p>ROOM FOR IM­PROVE­MENT</p>
    <p>You can­not take your art­work home im­me­di­ately as it takes time to dry. Pay $25 for de­liv­ery or re­turn a few days later to col­lect it.</p>
    <p>INSIDER TIP</p>
    <p>Sure, go in with an open mind and “freestyle”. But have a look at art­works for in­spi­ra­tion be­fore you start.</p>
    <p>While over­alls and shoe cov­er­ings are pro­vided, a lit­tle bit of paint still ends up on our clothes, so wear some­thing you do not mind get­ting dirty.</p>
    <p>WILL WE BE BACK?</p>
    <p>For sure. Play­ing with paints is cathar­tic fun and we look for­ward to im­pro­vis­ing as a fam­ily.</p>

